Malawi's Benchmark Tea Price Dropped 16% at Auction Yesterday, Broker Says

-- B y   F r a n k   J o m o
-- 
2011-03-09T11:05:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/malawi-s-benchmark-tea-price-dropped-16-at-auction-yesterday-broker-says.html
The benchmark price of tea in  Malawi ,  Africa ’s largest producer of the crop after Kenya, fell
16 percent at auction yesterday to $2.15 a kilogram from $2.55 a
week earlier, Tea Brokers Central Africa, which manages the
country’s tea auctions, said in an e-mailed report today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Frank Jomo in Blantyre at 
 fjomo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
